Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.93,0:02:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們回到3萬年前 狗狗誕生前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's go back across 30,000 years to a time before dogs,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.84,0:02:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我們的祖先生活在最後一次冰河時代的無盡冬夜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when our ancestors lived in the endless winter of the last ice age.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.01,0:02:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先小規模的群居 遊蕩著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors were wanderers living in small bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.54,0:02:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他們睡在星空下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They slept beneath the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.85,0:02:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,星星就是他們的故事書  日曆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sky was their storybook, calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.15,0:02:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,生活指南\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an instruction manual for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.15,0:02:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,星星告訴他們嚴寒何時到來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It told them when the bitter colds would come,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.86,0:02:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,穀物何時成熟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the wild grains would ripen,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.86,0:02:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,鹿群和野牛群何時遷徙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the herds of caribou and bison would be on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.46,0:02:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他們對家的印象就是地球本身\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their idea of home was Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.46,0:02:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他們受到其他飢餓生物的威脅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But they lived in fear of other hungry creatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.20,0:02:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,比如獅子和熊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the mountain lions and the bears
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.34,0:03:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,與他們搶奪同樣地獵物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that competed with them for the same prey
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.97,0:03:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,還有狼群會掠食他們中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the wolves that threatened to carry off and devour
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.74,0:03:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,最脆弱的同伴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the most vulnerable among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.10,0:03:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的狼都想來分一杯羹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All the wolves want to get at the bone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.07,0:03:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但大部分都不敢靠的太近\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but most of them are too frightened to come close enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.67,0:03:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的恐懼來自血液中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their fear is due to high levels
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.17,0:03:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,高濃度的應激激素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of stress hormones in their blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.01,0:03:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,這是生死攸關的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a matter of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.91,0:03:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,因為靠的太近可能很致命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because coming too close to humans can be fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但也有些狼  因為自然差異\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But a few wolves-- due to natural variations--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.91,0:03:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,這種激素濃度較低\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have lower levels of those hormones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.72,0:03:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,使得他們不是那麼懼怕人類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This makes them less afraid of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.06,0:03:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,這頭狼和他祖先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This wolf has discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,中的一個分支發現了同樣的情況\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what a branch of his ancestors figured out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.19,0:03:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,大約在1萬5千年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}some 15,000 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.19,0:03:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,一個完美的生存策略\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an excellent survival strategy;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.20,0:04:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,人類的馴化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the domestication of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.47,0:04:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在人類捕獵時別威脅到他們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let the humans do the hunting, don't threaten them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.04,0:04:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他們會允許你以殘渣為食\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and they'll let you scavenge their garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你吃的更規律 就可以繁衍更多的後代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You'll eat more regularly, you'll leave more offspring,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.24,0:04:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,這些後代會繼承你的性情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and those offspring will inherit your disposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.08,0:04:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,這種馴養的淘汰方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This selection for tameness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.48,0:04:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,效果逐代加強\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would be reinforced with each generation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.62,0:04:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,直到這一系的野狼進化為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until that line of wild wolves evolves into...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.46,0:04:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,狗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.56,0:04:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以稱它為最友善的生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You might call this "survival of the friendliest."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.93,0:04:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,現在看來 這也是對人類非常有利的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Then as now, this was a good deal for the humans, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,那些吃剩飯的狗並不只是收拾垃圾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The scavenging dogs weren't just a sanitation squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.57,0:04:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他們也是保安力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They worked security.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.79,0:05:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,隨著這種不同物種間的合作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As this interspecies partnership continued over time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.16,0:05:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,狗的外貌也發生了改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the dogs' appearance changed also.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.86,0:05:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,可愛變成了優勝劣汰時的優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cuteness became a selective advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.13,0:05:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你越可愛 就有更大的機會活下去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The more adorable you were, the better chance you had
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.67,0:05:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,並把你的基因傳遞給下一代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to live and pass on your genes to another generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.10,0:05:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,起先是為了便利而結成的聯盟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What began as an alliance of convenience
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.11,0:05:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,變成了越來越深厚的友誼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}became a friendship that deepened over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.38,0:05:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,接下來發生了什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To see what happens next,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.01,0:05:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我們略過2萬年前的先祖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}let's leave our distant ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.48,0:05:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,看看不是很久以前的古人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of some 20,000 years ago to visit the more recent past
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.79,0:05:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在冰河時代的間歇期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}during an intermission in the Ice Age.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.66,0:05:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,平和的氣候帶來了一場變革\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This break in the climate starts a revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.46,0:05:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,人類不再流浪  而是定居下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Instead of wandering, people are settling down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.13,0:05:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,新的事物出現了  村莊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's something new in the world... villages.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.07,0:05:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,人們依然在打獵和採集食物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}People still hunt and gather,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.80,0:05:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但也開始了製造食物和衣服\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but now they also produce food and clothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.47,0:05:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,農業\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}agriculture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.68,0:05:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,狼用他們的自由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The wolves have traded their freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.98,0:05:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,來交換穩定的食物供應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in exchange for a steady meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.42,0:06:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,他們放棄了選擇夥伴的權利\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They've given up their right to choose a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.19,0:06:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,人類替他們選擇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now the humans choose for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.22,0:06:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,他們消滅無法被馴服的狗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They consistently kill off the dogs that can't be trained;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.33,0:06:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,那些會咬人的狗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the ones that bite the feeding hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.03,0:06:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他們繁育那些討喜的狗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And they breed the dogs that please them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.27,0:06:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,讓這些狗服從命令\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They nurture those dogs that do their bidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.41,0:06:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,打獵  放牧  守衛  拖拽重物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}hunting, herding, guarding, hauling,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.61,0:06:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,陪伴人類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and keeping them company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.71,0:06:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,從每一窩小狗中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From every litter,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.35,0:06:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,選擇那些他們最喜歡的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the humans select the puppies they like best.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.35,0:06:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,一代接一代 狗進化了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over the generations, the dogs evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,稱之為 人工選擇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This kind of evolution is called "artificial selection"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.26,0:06:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,或者  飼養\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or "breeding."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,把狼變成狗 是人類第一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Turning wolves into dogs was the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.06,0:06:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,親手干預進化過程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we humans took evolution into our own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.23,0:06:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,從那以後我們改進了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And we've been doing it ever since
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.36,0:06:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,對我們有用的植物和動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to shape all the plants and animals that we depend on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.47,0:06:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,彈指一揮間 大約1萬5千到2萬年裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In a blink of cosmic time, just 15,000 or 20,000 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.64,0:06:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我們把灰狼改變成為了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we turned gray wolves into all the kinds of dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:06:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,各種各樣的可愛的狗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we love today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.44,0:06:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,想想看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,各個品種的狗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Every breed of dog you've ever seen
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.98,0:07:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,都是人類塑造出來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was sculpted by human hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.78,0:07:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,其中大部分 最受歡迎的品種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Many of our best friends-- the most popular breeds--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,都是最近幾百年培育出來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were created in only the last few centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.79,0:07:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,進化的強大力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The awesome power of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.90,0:07:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,將窮兇極惡的狼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}transformed the ravenous wolf
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.50,0:07:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,變成忠心耿耿的牧羊犬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the faithful shepherd...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.13,0:07:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,保護 看守羊群 並驅趕狼群\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...who protects the herd and drives the wolf away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.82,0:07:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,人工培育 把狼變成狗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Artificial selection turned the wolf into the shepherd
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.15,0:07:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,把野草變成小麥和玉米\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the wild grasses into wheat and corn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.09,0:07:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上 大部分我們食用的植物和動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, almost every plant and animal that we eat today
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,都是來自野生的 不可食用的品種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was bred from a wild, less-edible ancestor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.33,0:07:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,如果強大的人工選擇可以在1萬到1萬5千年間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If artificial selection can work such profound changes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.97,0:07:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,帶來如此巨大的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in only 10,000 or 15,000 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:07:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼大自然的選擇淘汰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what can natural selection do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.87,0:08:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,在上百萬年間可以做到怎樣的程度呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}operating over billions of years?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,形形色色美好的生命就是答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The answer is all the beauty and diversity of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.95,0:08:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼做到得\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How does it work?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.88,0:08:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的想像之舟可以帶我們去任何地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our Ship of the Imagination can take us anywhere in space
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.99,0:08:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,任何時間 甚至看不見的小宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and time, even to the hidden microcosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.66,0:08:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,在哪裏 生命可以完成蛻變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where one kind of life can be transformed into another.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.70,0:08:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.42,0:08:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去可能不像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}May not seem like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.39,0:08:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我們曾經生活在冰河時期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but we've been living in an ice age
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.29,0:08:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,長達2百萬年之久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the last two million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.06,0:08:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,現在只是其中一個間歇期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This just happens to be one of the long intermissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.63,0:08:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,2百萬年間的大部分時期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For most of those two million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.43,0:08:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,氣候又冷又干\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the climate has been cold and dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.94,0:08:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,北極冰蓋比今天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The North Polar ice cap extended much farther south
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.67,0:08:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,所看到的範圍更大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than it does today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,在這漫長的冰川期\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In one of those long, cold glacial periods
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.24,0:08:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,從北極來的冬季海水冰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the winter sea ice stretched from the North Pole
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.15,0:08:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,一直延伸至今日洛杉磯所在的位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all the way down to what is now Los Angeles,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.65,0:09:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,大灰熊在冰凍荒蕪的愛爾蘭遊蕩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}great bears roamed the frozen wastes of Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.96,0:09:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,這頭熊看上去很普通\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This might look like an ordinary bear,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.76,0:09:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,但是她的內在卻有著不平凡的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but something extraordinary is happening inside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.10,0:09:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,一股催生新物種的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Something that will give rise to a new species.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.60,0:09:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,要探究這股力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In order to see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.27,0:09:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我們要把比例尺調整到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we'll need to descend down to a much smaller scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.64,0:09:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,細胞級別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the cellular level,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.61,0:09:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這樣才能探究熊的生殖系統\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so that we can explore the bear's reproductive system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.35,0:09:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我們通過鎖骨下的動脈穿過心臟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We'll take the subclavian artery through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.74,0:10:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,快到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.35,0:10:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一些她的卵子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those are some of her eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.92,0:10:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,要想瞭解這些卵子的詳情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To see what's going on in one of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.49,0:10:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我們必須變得更小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we'll have to get even smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.39,0:10:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,縮小到分子級別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We'll have to shrink down to the molecular level.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.36,0:10:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的想像之舟有多小呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our Ship of the Imagination is now so small,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.43,0:10:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一顆沙粒的百萬分之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you could fit a million of them into a grain of sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.37,0:10:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,看到那些闊步前進的小傢伙嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}See those guys over there strutting along those girders?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.34,0:10:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他們是蛋白質 叫做驅動蛋白\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They are proteins called kinesin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,這些驅動蛋白是搬運工\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These kinesin are part of the transport crew
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.35,0:10:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,忙碌地在細胞間傳遞貨物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that's busy moving cargo around the cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.18,0:10:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,長得就像外星人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How alien they seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.05,0:10:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他們和其他長相類似的小傢伙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And yet these tiny creatures-- and beings like them--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.86,0:10:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,存在於每個活細胞中 包括我們的細胞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are a part of every living cell, including the ones inside you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.53,0:10:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,如果生命體也有聖殿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If life has a sanctuary,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.23,0:11:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是細胞核 包含了我們的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's here in the nucleus which contains our DNA...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.10,0:11:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我們遺傳密碼的遠古聖經\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the ancient scripture of our genetic code.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.81,0:11:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,由所有生命體都能理解的語言寫成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's written in a language that all life can read.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.39,0:11:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,DNA是一種長螺旋階梯狀的分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}DNA is a molecule shaped like a long twisted ladder
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.12,0:11:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,也叫雙螺旋結構\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or double helix.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.29,0:11:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,階梯的橫檔是由4種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The rungs of the ladder are made
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.09,0:11:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,不同的小分子組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of four different kinds of smaller molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.43,0:11:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,這些就是基因字母表中的字母\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These are the letters of the genetic alphabet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.43,0:11:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,這些字母的特定排列組合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Particular arrangements of those letters spell out
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.40,0:11:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,產生出針對所有生命體的指令\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the instructions for all living things,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.84,0:11:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,告訴他們如果生長 移動 消化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}telling them how to grow, move, digest,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.27,0:11:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,感知環境 癒合 繁殖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sense the environment, heal, reproduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.78,0:11:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,DNA雙螺旋就是一台分子機器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The DNA double helix is a molecular machine
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,由1千億稱之為原子的部件組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with about 100 billion parts called "atoms."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.02,0:11:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,單個DNA分子中的原子數量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are as many atoms in a single molecule of your DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.62,0:11:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,多的就像銀河系中的繁星數量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as there are stars in a typical galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.43,0:11:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,和狗一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The same is true for dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.53,0:12:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,和熊一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and bears
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.13,0:12:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,和所有生物一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and every living thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.60,0:12:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我們 每一個人 就是一個小宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We are, each of us, a little universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,DNA信息在細胞與細胞間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The DNA message handed down from cell to cell
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.32,0:12:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,也在一代接一代的繁衍中異常謹慎地複製著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and from generation to generation is copied with extreme care.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.19,0:12:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,當一條鬆開的蛋白質分開雙螺旋的兩條邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The birth of a new DNA molecule begins when an unwinding protein
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.79,0:12:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,拆開中間的橫檔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}separates the two strands of the double helix,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.29,0:12:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,新的DNA分子就誕生了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}breaking the rungs apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,細胞核的液體中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Inside the liquid of the nucleus,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.53,0:12:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,遺傳密碼的分子字母自由的游動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the molecular letters of the genetic code float freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.47,0:12:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,雙螺旋的其中一邊複製著失去的另外一邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each strand of the helix copies its lost partner,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.87,0:12:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,變成兩個完全一樣的DNA分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}resulting in two identical DNA molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是生命體如果繁衍和傳遞基因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's how life reproduces genes and transmits them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.91,0:12:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,代代相傳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from one generation to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.98,0:12:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,當一個活細胞分裂成兩個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When a living cell divides in two,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,每個細胞都帶有一份完整的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}each one takes away with it a complete copy of the DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.09,0:13:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,一種特定的蛋白質負責校對\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A specialized protein proofreads to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.86,0:13:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,確保只接受正確的字母\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that only the right letters are accepted
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.69,0:13:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,這保證了DNA的準確複製\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so that the DNA is accurately copied.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.56,0:13:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,但是沒有什麼是完美的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But nobody's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.33,0:13:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,偶爾 校對也會發生失誤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Occasionally, a proofreading error slips through,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.53,0:13:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,在遺傳指令中產生了細微的隨機變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}making a small, random change in the genetic instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.34,0:13:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,這頭熊的卵子細胞中發生了突變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A mutation has occurred in the bear's egg cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.57,0:13:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,如此細微的隨機事件也會帶來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A random event as tiny as this one can have consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,很大的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on a far grander scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.78,0:13:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,突變改變了控制毛皮顏色的基因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That mutation altered the gene that controls fur color.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.62,0:13:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,它影響了這只熊的後代的深色毛皮的產生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It will affect the production of dark pigment in the fur
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.62,0:13:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,它影響了這只熊的後代的深色毛皮的產生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the bear's offspring.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.63,0:13:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,大多數突變是無害的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most mutations are harmless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.93,0:13:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,有些是致命的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some are deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,少數 純屬偶然 使得某個生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But a few, purely by chance, can give an organism
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.60,0:13:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,在競爭中獲得重大優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a critical advantage over the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.30,0:13:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,1年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A year has passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.31,0:13:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,這只熊做了母親\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our bear is now a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.14,0:13:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,作為突變的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And as a result of that mutation,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.88,0:13:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,其中一隻熊寶寶生來就是白色的皮毛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one of her two cubs was born with a white coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:13:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,當兩隻熊長大到可以自己獵食時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the cubs get old enough to venture out on their own,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.28,0:14:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,哪頭熊更可能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which bear is more likely
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.58,0:14:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,悄悄地接近他們的獵物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to be able to sneak up on unsuspecting prey?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.79,0:14:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,棕熊和雪區別明顯  很遠就能被察覺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The brown bear can be seen against the snow a mile away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,白熊子孫滿堂 並把他獨特的基因\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The white bear prospers and passes on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.96,0:14:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,傳遞下去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its own particular set of genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.93,0:14:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,這樣的情況不斷發生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This happens repeatedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.80,0:14:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,再接下去的幾代裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over succeeding generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.97,0:14:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,白色皮毛的基因散播遍及整個北極的熊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the gene for white fur spreads through the entire population of Arctic bears.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.24,0:14:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,深色皮毛的基因消亡在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The gene for dark fur loses out
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.98,0:14:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,生存的競爭中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the competition for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.75,0:14:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,突變是完全隨機並且時刻發生的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mutations are entirely random and happen all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.65,0:14:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,但是環境會對獎勵那些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the environment rewards those
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,對生存有利的突變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that increase the chance for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.92,0:14:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,大自然選擇那些可以更好適應環境的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It naturally selects the living things that are better suited to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.99,0:14:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,這種選擇絕對不是隨機的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that selection is the opposite of random.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.63,0:14:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,兩個種群的熊各自分開\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The two populations of bears separated,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.14,0:14:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,經過了上千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and over thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.00,0:14:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,進化出各自獨有的特徵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}evolved other characteristics that set them apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.17,0:15:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他們變成了不同的物種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They became different species.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是查爾斯 達爾文所說的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's what Charles Darwin meant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,物種起源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by "the origin of species."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.55,0:15:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,單個的熊不會進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}An individual bear doesn't evolve;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,一群熊在幾代繁衍中進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the population of bears evolves over generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.73,0:15:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,如果北極的冰日益減少\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If the Arctic ice continues to dwindle
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.83,0:15:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,全球變暖的緣故 北極熊可能滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}due to global warming, the polar bears may go extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.53,0:15:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,他們會被棕熊取代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They'll be replaced by brown bears,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.57,0:15:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,可以更好地適應冰融後的環境\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}better adapted to the now defrosted environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.74,0:15:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,這個故事和狗的進化不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is a different story from the one about the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.24,0:15:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有人去指導這個變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No breeder guided these changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.74,0:15:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他們都是由自然環境選擇的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Instead, the environment itself selects them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.25,0:15:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是物競天擇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is evolution by natural selection,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,科學歷史上最顛覆性的理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the most revolutionary concept in the history of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.72,0:15:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,1859年 達爾文首次提出了支持這個理論的證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Darwin first presented the evidence for this idea in 1859.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.89,0:15:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,它帶來的爭議從未消退\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The uproar it caused has never subsided.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.73,0:16:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我們都可以理解那種令人不適的刺痛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We all understand the twinge of discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.86,0:16:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是由猩猩進化而來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the thought that we share a common ancestor with the apes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.13,0:16:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們的想法裏 親戚 最能讓我們感到丟臉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No one can embarrass you like a relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.50,0:16:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的近親  黑猩猩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our closest ones, the chimpanzees,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.70,0:16:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他們頻繁在公共場合做出不當的舉止\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they frequently behave inappropriately in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,人類想和他們保持距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's an understandable human need
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.64,0:16:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,也是可以理解的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to distance ourselves from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.88,0:16:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,傳統信仰的核心前提\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A central premise of traditional belief
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.15,0:16:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是造物者特製的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is that we were created separately
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,和其他動物有區別的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from all the other animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.15,0:16:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,這種觀點也很容易被理解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's easy to see why this idea has taken hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,它讓我們覺得 與眾不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It makes us feel... special.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.76,0:16:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們和這些樹是親戚呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what about our kinship with the trees?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.86,0:16:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你又作何感想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How does that make you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.94,0:16:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,這是橡樹DNA的一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, here's a segment of the oak tree's DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.21,0:16:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,把它看做條形碼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of it like a bar code.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.38,0:16:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,生命代碼的指令\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The instructions written in the code of life
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.01,0:16:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,告訴這個樹如何分解糖分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tell the tree how to metabolize sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.01,0:17:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,拿它和我自己的DNA作比較\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now let's compare it with the same section of my own DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.52,0:17:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,DNA不會撒謊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The DNA doesn't lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.46,0:17:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,這棵樹就是我失散已久的表親\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This tree and me-- we're long-lost cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.79,0:17:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,不單單是樹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's not just the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.80,0:17:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,如果回到很久以前 我們可以發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you go back far enough, you'll find that we share
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.70,0:17:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我們有著共同的祖先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a common ancestor with...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.74,0:17:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,蝴蝶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the butterfly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.07,0:17:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,灰狼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}gray wolf...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.70,0:17:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,蘑菇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}mushroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.11,0:17:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,鯊魚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.74,0:17:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,細菌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}bacterium...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.21,0:17:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,麻雀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sparrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.54,0:17:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,多麼幸福的一家人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What a family!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,條形碼的其他部分因人而異\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Other parts of the bar code vary from species to species.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.65,0:17:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這也使得貓頭鷹和章魚有所區別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's what makes the difference between an owl and an octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.89,0:17:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,除非你有一個同卵雙胞胎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unless you have an identical twin,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.12,0:17:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,這個世界上不會有人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there's no one else in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.42,0:17:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,和你有著相同的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14} with the exact same DNA as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.09,0:17:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,其他的物種中 遺傳基因的不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Within other species, the genetic differences
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,為自然選擇提供了原材料\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}provide the raw material for natural selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.73,0:17:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,環境決定了什麼基因可以生存繁衍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The environment selects which genes survive and multiply.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.67,0:17:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,說到生物遺傳基因的指令中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When it comes to the genetic instructions for life's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.84,0:17:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,最基本的功能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}most basic functions--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,比方說分解糖分  我們和其他物種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}say, digesting sugars-- we and other species
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.64,0:18:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎一致\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are almost identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,因為這些是生命最基本的功能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's because those functions are so basic to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.81,0:18:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他們在各種不同生命形式誕生前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they evolved before the various life-forms
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.75,0:18:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,就已經進化完成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}branched off from each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.75,0:18:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是我們的生命之樹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is our Tree of Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.22,0:18:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,科學使我們可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science has made it possible
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.76,0:18:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,為地球上的所有生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for us to construct this family tree
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.93,0:18:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,繪製這份家譜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for all the species of life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.93,0:18:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,相近基因的親戚住在同一根的枝幹上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Close genetic relatives occupy the same branch of the tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,差異越大住得越遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}while more distant cousins are farther away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.40,0:18:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,每根細枝都是一個物種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Each twig is a living species.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.57,0:18:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,主桿代表著地球上所有生命的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the trunk of the tree represents the common ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.78,0:18:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,共同祖先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of all life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.61,0:18:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,生命具有很高的可塑性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stuff of life is so malleable
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.01,0:18:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,生命一旦出現  環境就開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that once it got started, the environment molded it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.98,0:18:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,將它塑造出驚人數量的不同形態\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a staggering variety of forms--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.29,0:18:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,比我們所能展示的還多1萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}10,000 times more than we can possibly show here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.09,0:18:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,生物學家已經編錄了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Biologists have catalogued
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.26,0:18:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,50萬種不同的甲殼蟲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a half a million different kinds of beetles alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.47,0:19:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,更別提那些數之不盡的細菌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not to mention the numberless varieties of bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.77,0:19:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,有幾百萬種不同種類的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are many millions of living species
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.14,0:19:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,動物和植物  其中大部分依然未知\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of animals and plants,  most of them still unknown to science.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.95,0:19:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,這麼說吧  我們至今還沒有見過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of that-- we have yet to make contact
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.05,0:19:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的陸棲生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with most of the forms of terrestrial life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.39,0:19:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我們這個小小星球上就是有這麼多種的生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's how many kinds of life there are on this tiny planet alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.56,0:19:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,生命之樹將觸角伸向所有的方向\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Tree of Life extends its feelers in all directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.13,0:19:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,探尋可行的辦法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}finding and exploiting what works,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.73,0:19:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,為新的生命形式創造新的環境和機會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}creating new environments and opportunities for new forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.87,0:19:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,生命之樹已經35億歲了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Tree of Life is three and a half billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.64,0:19:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,時間已經長的可以發展出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's plenty of time to develop
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.84,0:19:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,所有令人驚奇的本領\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an impressive repertoire of tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.42,0:19:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,進化可以使一種動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Evolution can disguise an animal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.08,0:19:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,偽裝成植物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a plant...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.02,0:19:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,花費了數千代的努力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...taking thousands of generations
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.03,0:20:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,去設計一套精心製作的服飾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to contrive an elaborate costume
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.20,0:20:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,用來欺騙捕食者的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that fools predators into looking elsewhere for someone to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.60,0:20:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,或者植物偽裝成動物的模樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Or it can disguise a plant as an animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.60,0:20:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,花朵進化出黃蜂般的外表\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}evolving blossoms that take on the appearance of a wasp--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.74,0:20:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,蘭花就用這種方式誘使黃蜂為他授粉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the orchid's way of fooling real wasps into pollinating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.78,0:20:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是強大的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the awesome
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.88,0:20:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,自然選擇下的變形本領\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}shape-shifting power of natural selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.03,0:20:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在密集雜亂的巨大生命之樹上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Among the dense, tangled limbs of the vast Tree of Life...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.73,0:20:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.90,0:20:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,數不勝數的眾多分支中的一小支\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One tiny branch among countless millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.20,0:20:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,科學揭示了所有生命本是同源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science reveals that all life on Earth is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.29,0:20:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,達爾文發現真正的進化機制\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Darwin discovered the actual mechanisof evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.91,0:20:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,過去普遍的觀點是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The prevailing belief was that the complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.67,0:21:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,種類繁多的生命必然是有造物主創造的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and variety of life must be the work of an intelligent designer,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.67,0:21:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,分別創造了幾百萬種不同的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who created each of these millions of different species separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.93,0:21:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,它認為 生物實在是太複雜了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Living things are just too intricate, it was said,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.43,0:21:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,不可能由未經引導的進化而來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to be the result of unguided evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.00,0:21:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,就像人的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Consider the human eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.47,0:21:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,一個極其複雜的傑作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a masterpiece of complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.37,0:21:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,要有角膜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It requires a cornea,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.51,0:21:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,虹膜 晶狀體 視網膜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}iris, lens, retina,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.98,0:21:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,視神經 肌肉群\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}optic nerves, muscles,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.38,0:21:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,再配合大腦複製的神經網絡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}let alone the brain's elaborate neural network
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.12,0:21:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,才能產生一幅圖像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to interpret images.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.06,0:21:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,它遠比其他任何一個人類製造的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's more complicated than any device
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.96,0:21:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,物體要來的複雜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ever crafted by human intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.06,0:21:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 結論是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Therefore, it was argued,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.73,0:21:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,人眼不可能是無意識的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the human eye can't be the result
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,進化產物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of mindless evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.13,0:21:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,要瞭解真相 我們需要回到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To know if that's true, we need to travel across time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.17,0:21:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我們有能力看之前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a world before there were eyes to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.41,0:22:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,最初 所有生物都看不見任何東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the beginning, life was blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.75,0:22:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,這是我們的世界 40億年前的樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is what our world looked like four billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.76,0:22:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那時 生物還無法產生視覺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before there were any eyes to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.43,0:22:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,直到幾億年過去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until a few hundred million years passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.50,0:22:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,突然有一天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and then, one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.63,0:22:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,一個細菌的DNA產生了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there was a microscopic copying error
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.70,0:22:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,細微的複製錯誤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the DNA of a bacterium.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.27,0:22:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,這個隨機的突變給了這個微生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This random mutation gave that microbe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.01,0:22:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,一個可以吸收陽光的蛋白質分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a protein molecule that absorbed sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.81,0:22:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,想知道感光細菌的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Want to know what the world looked like
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.65,0:22:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,是什麼樣子的嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a light-sensitive bacterium?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.07,0:22:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,看看屏幕的右邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Take a look at the right side of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.36,0:22:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,突變繼續隨機的發生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mutations continued to occur at random,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.29,0:22:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在其他所有的生物身上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as they always do in any population of living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.53,0:22:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,另一個突變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Another mutation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.66,0:23:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,使得細菌可以逃離強烈的陽光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}caused a dark bacterium to flee intense light.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.63,0:23:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,發生了什麼事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What is going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.03,0:23:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,黑夜和白晝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Night and day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.80,0:23:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,這些可以區分亮光的細菌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those bacteria that could tell light from dark
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.84,0:23:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,相對其他細菌有了一個決定性的優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had a decisive advantage over the ones that couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.51,0:23:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.34,0:23:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,因為日光帶著強烈的紫外線會損傷DNA\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because the daytime brought harsh, ultraviolet light that damages DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.48,0:23:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,敏感的細菌避開強烈的光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sensitive bacteria fled the intense light
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.55,0:23:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,在暗處安全的交換\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to safely exchange their DNA in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.09,0:23:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他們比其他生活在表面的細菌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They survived in greater numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.02,0:23:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,更多的存活下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than the bacteria that stayed at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.49,0:23:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,日積月累 這些光敏蛋白質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over time, those light-sensitive proteins
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.60,0:23:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在更高級的單細胞生物身上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}became concentrated in a pigment spot
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.23,0:23:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,濃縮成一個色素點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the more advanced, one-celled organism.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.53,0:23:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這使尋找光亮成為可能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This made it possible to find the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.74,0:23:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,對於需要陽光合成食物的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an overwhelming advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.87,0:23:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,生命體來說 這是個壓倒性的優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for an organism that harvests sunlight to make food.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.28,0:23:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,這是扁平蟲眼中的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here's a flatworm's-eye view of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.22,0:23:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,這個多細胞生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This multi-celled organism
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.39,0:24:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,在色素點中進化出一個小坑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}evolved a dimple in the pigment spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.72,0:24:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,碗狀的凹痕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The bowl-shaped depression
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.03,0:24:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,使動物可以區別明暗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}allowed the animal to distinguish light from shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.40,0:24:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,大致看出周圍的物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to crudely make out objects in its vicinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.77,0:24:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,包括食物和天敵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including those to eat and those that might eat it...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.80,0:24:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,非常了不起的優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a tremendous advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.37,0:24:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,隨後 影像更清晰了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Later, things became a little clearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.04,0:24:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,小坑變深了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The dimple deepened
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.78,0:24:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,進化成一個有開口的凹槽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and evolved into a socket with a small opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.55,0:24:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,經過幾千代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over thousands of generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.92,0:24:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,自然選擇逐漸塑造出眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}natural selection was slowly sculpting the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.92,0:24:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,開放的地方凝聚成一個小孔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The opening contracted to a pinhole covered
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.09,0:24:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,由一層保護性的透明薄膜覆蓋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by a protective transparent membrane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.43,0:24:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,只允許一點點的光線透過小孔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only a little light could enter the tiny hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.93,0:24:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,但也足夠在敏感的眼睛內部表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it was enough to paint a dim image
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.33,0:24:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,描繪出一幅模糊的圖像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the sensitive inner surface of the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.90,0:24:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,這演變出了聚焦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This sharpened the focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.80,0:24:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,更大的孔可以讓更多的光線通過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A larger opening would have let in more light
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.14,0:24:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,產生更亮的圖像  但卻失去了焦點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to make a brighter image but one that was out of focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.74,0:24:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,這個新形態引發了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This development launched the visual equivalent
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.65,0:24:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,視覺的軍備競賽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of an arms race.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.69,0:25:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,競爭者們需要跟上才能生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The competition needed to keep up to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.30,0:25:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,一個新的絕妙特徵出現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But then a splendid new feature of the eye evolved,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.03,0:25:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,可以同時保證亮度和清晰焦點的晶狀體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a lens that provided both brightness and sharp focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.04,0:25:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,在遠古的魚類眼中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the eyes of primitive fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.47,0:25:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,小孔附近的透明膠體形成了晶狀體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the transparent gel near the pinhole formed into a lens.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.21,0:25:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,同時 小孔擴大了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At the same time, the pinhole enlarged
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.98,0:25:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,允許更多的光線通過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to let in more and more light.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.05,0:25:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,魚的視界高清了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fish could now see in high-def,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.48,0:25:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,不論遠近\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}both close up and far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.22,0:25:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 可怕的事情發生了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And then something terrible happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.86,0:25:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你注意到一杯水中的吸管\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Have you ever noticed that a straw in a glass of water
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.36,0:25:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去在水面處是彎的嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}looks bent at the surface of the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.86,0:25:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那是因為光線從一個介質進入另一個介質時發生了折射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's because light bends when it goes from one medium
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.63,0:25:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,就像從水到空氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to another, say from water to air.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.54,0:25:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的眼睛最初是為了在水中視物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our eyes originally evolved to see in water.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.31,0:26:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,眼中的水狀液體巧妙地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The watery fluid in those eyes neatly
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.21,0:26:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,消除了折射的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}eliminated the distortion of that bending effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.98,0:26:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但是對於陸地動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But for land animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.18,0:26:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,在空氣中成像的光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the light carries images from dry air
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.59,0:26:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,進入他們濕潤的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into their still-watery eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.69,0:26:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,光線發生折射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That bends the light rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.26,0:26:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,造成全面的失真\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}causing all kinds of distortions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.26,0:26:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,當我們的兩棲祖先從水中登陸時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When our amphibious ancestors left the water for the land,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.03,0:26:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,原本在水中精確視物的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their eyes, exquisitely evolved to see in water,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.27,0:26:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,卻在空氣中一塌糊塗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were lousy for seeing in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.60,0:26:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,從那時起我們的視力一直不好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our vision has never been as good since.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.27,0:26:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我們一直認為我們的眼睛是最高級的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We like to think of our eyes as state-of-the-art,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.21,0:26:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,但直到3.75億年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but 375 million years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.11,0:26:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我們依然無法看清近在眼前的東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we still can't see things right in front of our noses
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.55,0:26:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,或者像魚那樣在昏暗環境中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or discern fine details in near darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.22,0:26:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,能夠辨別細節\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the way fish can.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.12,0:26:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,當我們離開水裏時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When we left the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.62,0:26:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼大自然不能從新來過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}why didn't nature just start over again
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.79,0:26:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,進化出一對新的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and evolve us a new set of eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.42,0:26:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,可以在空氣中清晰視物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that were optimal for seeing in the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.76,0:26:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,大自然並不是這樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nature doesn't work that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.86,0:26:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,進化過程對於已有的結構的改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Evolution reshapes existing structures over generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.27,0:26:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是世世代代的慢慢適應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}adapting them with small changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.47,0:27:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,而不可能一切都\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can't just go back to the drawing board
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.14,0:27:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,推倒重來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and start from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.97,0:27:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,進化中眼睛 在每一步的發展中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At every stage of its development, the evolving eye
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.54,0:27:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,都為我們的生存提供了極大的優勢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}functioned well enough to provide a selective advantage for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.45,0:27:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,在現在存活的動物身上 我們發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And among animals alive today, we find eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.32,0:27:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,各個發展階段的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at all these stages of development.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.76,0:27:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,他們都很實用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And all of them function.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.09,0:27:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,人類眼睛的複雜程度對進化過程來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The complexity of the human eye poses
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.26,0:27:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有絲毫難度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no challenge to evolution by natural selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.27,0:27:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上 沒有進化就根本無法解釋眼睛和其他生物學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, the eye and all of biology makes no sense without evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.57,0:27:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,有人說進化論只是一種理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some claim that evolution is just a theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.24,0:27:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,只不過是一種觀點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as if it were merely an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.44,0:27:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,進化論就和萬有引力定律一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The theory of evolution, like the theory of gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.18,0:27:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,是科學的事實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a scientific fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.28,0:27:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,進化確有其事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Evolution really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.02,0:27:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,承認我們和其他生物出自同源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Accepting our kinship with all life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.45,0:27:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,並不只是嚴謹的科學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is not only solid science.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.52,0:27:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,在我看來 這也是一種崇高的心靈體驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In my view, it's also a soaring spiritual experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.97,0:28:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,因為進化是盲目地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because evolution is blind,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.84,0:28:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,它無法預測或改變悲劇的發生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it cannot anticipate or adapt to catastrophic events.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.11,0:28:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,生命之樹有一些斷裂的分支\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Tree of Life has some broken branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.94,0:28:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,其中大部分發生在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Many of them were severed in the five greatest catastrophes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.45,0:28:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,五次最大的災難中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that life has ever known.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.32,0:28:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,某個地方 有著一座紀念堂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Somewhere, there's a memorial
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.32,0:28:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,紀念著消失的物種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the multitude of lost species,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.32,0:28:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,滅絕物種的紀念堂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Halls of Extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.49,0:28:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,隨我來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.29,0:28:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.00,0:28:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}滅絕紀念堂
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.63,0:28:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,歡迎來到滅絕紀念堂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Welcome to the Halls of Extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.65,0:28:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,紀念著生命之樹上的斷枝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A monument to the broken branches of the Tree of Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.46,0:29:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,對於依然存在的上百萬種生物來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For every single one of the millions of species
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.20,0:29:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,可能上千種正在垂死掙扎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}alive today, perhaps a thousand others have perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.47,0:29:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,他們中大部分在與\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of them died out in the everyday competition
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.97,0:29:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,其他生命形式的日常競爭中絕種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with other life-forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.54,0:29:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,但也有很多是被地球上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But many of them were swept away in vast cataclysms
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.14,0:29:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,無法抗拒的大災難滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that overwhelmed the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.38,0:29:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,在過去的5億年裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the last 500 million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.81,0:29:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,發生過5次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this has happened five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.50,0:29:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}奧陶紀(地質時代中顯生宙古生代的第二個紀)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.00,0:29:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}泥盆紀(地質時代古生代中的第四個紀)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.70,0:29:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}三疊紀(中生代的第一個紀)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.30,0:29:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}白堊紀(地質年代中中生代的最後一個紀)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.00,0:29:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}二疊紀(古生代的最後一個地質時代)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.99,0:29:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.52,0:29:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,5次滅絕地球生命的大災難\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Five mass extinctions that devastated life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.72,0:29:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,最慘的一次發生在2.5億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The worst one of all happened some 250 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.99,0:29:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,一個紀元的終結\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the end of an era
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.56,0:29:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,稱之 二疊紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}known as the Permian.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.38,0:29:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,三葉蟲像裝甲部隊一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Trilobites were armored animals that hunted
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.15,0:30:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,成群結隊的在海床上肆虐\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in great herds across the seafloor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.65,0:30:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他們是第一批進化出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were among the first animals to evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.35,0:30:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,可以成像的眼睛的動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}image-forming eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.33,0:30:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,三葉蟲繁榮了大約2.7億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Trilobites had a good long run, some 270 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.36,0:30:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,地球曾是三葉蟲的天下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth was once the planet of the trilobites.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.93,0:30:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,但他們現在都沒了 絕種了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But now they're all gone, extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.37,0:30:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,他們中最後的一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The last of them were swept from life's stage
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.11,0:30:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,也隨著其他物種一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}along with countless other species
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.21,0:30:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,在空前的環境災難中絕種了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in an unparalleled environmental disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.96,0:30:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,大災難發生在今日西伯利亞的位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The apocalypse began in what is now Siberia,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.59,0:30:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,一場人類史上規模無比巨大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with volcanic eruptions on a scale unlike anything
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.26,0:30:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,的火山噴發\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.88,0:31:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,那時地球很不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth was very different then,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.45,0:31:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一個超質大陸板塊和一片大洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with one single supercontinent and one great ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.78,0:31:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,無情的滾燙的熔漿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Relentless floods of fiery lava
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.29,0:31:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,洪水般吞沒了比西歐還大的區域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}engulfed an area larger than Western Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.09,0:31:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,斷斷續續的噴發持續了幾十萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The pulsing eruptions went on for hundreds of thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.96,0:31:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,融化的岩石\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The molten rock
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.56,0:31:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,點燃了煤層 並且 污染了大氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ignited coal deposits and polluted the air
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.30,0:31:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,充斥著二氧化碳和其他溫室氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with carbon dioxide and other greenhouse gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.96,0:31:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,地球溫度升高 洋流停止了流動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This heated the Earth and stopped the ocean currents from circulating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.36,0:31:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,有害的細菌迅速繁殖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Noxious bacteria bloomed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.69,0:31:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,海中其他生物幾乎全部滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but nearly everything else in the seas died.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.86,0:31:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,腐臭的水散發出致命的硫化氫氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stagnant waters belched deadly hydrogen sulfide gas into the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.93,0:31:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,導致大多數陸地生物窒息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which suffocated most of the land animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.48,0:32:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,百分之九十的物種滅絕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nine in ten of all species on the planet went extinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.85,0:32:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱之為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.96,0:32:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"大滅絕"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Great Dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.70,0:32:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的生命差一點全部絕種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Life on Earth came so near to being wiped out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.78,0:32:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,需要花費上千萬年才能恢復\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that it took more than ten million years to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.08,0:32:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但是新的生命形式在慢慢進化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But new life-forms slowly evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.41,0:32:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,開始填補由二疊紀大屠殺遺留的空缺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to fill the openings left by the Permian holocaust.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.86,0:32:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,恐龍就是其中的大贏家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Among the biggest winners were the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.76,0:32:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,現在地球是他們的天下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now the Earth was their planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.60,0:33:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的統治持續了1.5億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their reign continued for over 150 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.87,0:33:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,也是在一次大災難中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until it, too, came crashing down
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.50,0:33:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,不可避免的土崩瓦解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in another mass extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的生命從太古時期就飽受摧殘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Life on Earth has taken quite a beating over the eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.08,0:33:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,卻依然存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And yet it's still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.91,0:33:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,生命頑強得令人驚訝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The tenacity of life is mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.75,0:33:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我們總是能找到一條意想不到的生存之路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We keep finding it where no one thought it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.02,0:33:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,看到那條無名走廊嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That nameless corridor?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.36,0:33:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,以後再說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's for another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.34,0:33:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,有種動物可以活在沸騰的水中或者堅固的冰層中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I know an animal that can live in boiling water or in solid ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.64,0:33:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,可以10年不喝一滴水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can go ten years without a drop of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.04,0:33:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,可以不加防護的穿過寒冷真空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It can travel naked in the cold vacuum
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.71,0:33:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,並且充滿強烈輻射的太空 而毫髮無損\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and intense radiation of space and will return unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.25,0:33:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,節肢動物 又叫  緩步類動物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The tardigrade, or water bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.72,0:33:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,生活在最高的高山還是最深的海溝\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's equally at home atop the tallest mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.82,0:33:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,對他們來說沒有區別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and in the deepest trenches of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.66,0:34:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,他們生活在苔蘚中  就在我們周圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And in our own backyards, where they live among the moss
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.73,0:34:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,數也數不清\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in countless numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.23,0:34:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能從沒注意到他們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You've probably never noticed them
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.63,0:34:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,因為他們太小了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because they're so small.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.13,0:34:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,差不多針尖大小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}About the size of a pinpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.77,0:34:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但他們很堅韌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But they're tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.50,0:34:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,節肢動物在所有的5次大災難中倖存下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The tardigrades have survived all five mass extinctions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.81,0:34:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,而他們則存在了5億年之久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They've been in business for a half a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.57,0:34:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我們一直認為生命很挑剔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We used to think that life was finicky,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.94,0:34:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,他只能接受\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that it would only take hold where it was
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.91,0:34:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,不太冷 不太熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not too hot, not too cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.91,0:34:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,不太暗 不咸 不酸 沒輻射 的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not too dark or salty or acidic or radioactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.68,0:34:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,還有 不管怎麼樣 別忘了喝水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And whatever you do, don't forget to add water.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.49,0:34:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我們錯了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.26,0:34:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,節肢動物證明我們錯了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As the hardy tardigrade demonstrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.59,0:34:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,生命可以承受人類絕對無法生存的環境\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}life can endure conditions that would mean certain death for us humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.03,0:34:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我們和那些生活在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But differences between us and life found
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.86,0:34:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,最極端環境下的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in even the most extreme environments on our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.43,0:34:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,只有少許的區別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are only variations on a single theme,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.44,0:34:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,就像一種語言中的不同方言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}dialects of a single language.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.01,0:34:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,地球生命的遺傳密碼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The genetic code of Earth life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.71,0:34:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,其他世界的生命又是什麼樣的呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what would life be like on other worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.28,0:35:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,有著完全不同歷史的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Worlds with a completely different history,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.32,0:35:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,和我們完全不同的化學反應和進化過程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}chemistry and evolution from our planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.79,0:35:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我想帶你去一個遙遠的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a distant world I want to take you to--
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.36,0:35:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,一個和我們這個截然不同的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a world far different from our own,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.80,0:35:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,可能藏有生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but one that may harbor life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.17,0:35:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有 那絕對我們以前見過的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If it does, it promises to be unlike anything
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.07,0:35:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,大不相同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we've ever seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.12,0:35:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,雲霧完全包裹了泰坦的表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Clouds and haze completely hide the surface of Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.12,0:35:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即土衛六
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.52,0:35:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,土星的大月亮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Saturn's giant moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.52,0:35:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,泰坦和地球有點像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Titan reminds me a little bit of home.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.13,0:35:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他也有主要以氮氣組成的大氣層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like Earth, it has an atmosphere that's mostly nitrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.63,0:35:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,但是比我們的稠密4倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it's four times denser.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.80,0:35:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,空氣中沒有絲毫氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Titan's air has no oxygen at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.70,0:36:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,比地球上任何地方都冷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's far colder than anywhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.20,0:36:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我依然想去那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But still... I want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.98,0:36:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我們必須下降\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We have to descend
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.51,0:36:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,幾百公里的煙霧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through a couple hundred kilometers of smog
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.98,0:36:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,才能看到他的表面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before we can even see the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.98,0:36:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,但是下面藏著我們熟悉的風景\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But hidden beneath lies a weirdly familiar landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.23,0:36:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,泰坦是太陽系中除地球外唯一一個會下雨的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Titan is the only other world in the solar system where it ever rains.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.17,0:36:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,它有著河流和海岸線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It has rivers and coastlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.51,0:36:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,有幾百個湖泊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Titan has hundreds of lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.61,0:36:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有一個比北美的蘇必利爾湖還大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One of them larger than Lake Superior in North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.18,0:36:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,蒸汽從湖面升起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Vapor rising from the lakes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.18,0:36:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,凝結落下變成雨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}condenses and falls again as rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.42,0:36:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,就像地球一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The rain feeds rivers,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.36,0:36:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,雨落進河流\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which carve valleys into the landscape,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.69,0:36:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,河流再將山谷雕刻出風景\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just like on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.96,0:37:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,但有一個很大不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But with one big difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.07,0:37:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,泰坦上 海和雨不是由甲烷和乙烷組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On Titan, the seas and the rain
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.80,0:37:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are made not of water but of methane and ethane.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.74,0:37:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,在地球上 這些分子組成天然氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On Earth, those molecules form natural gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.71,0:37:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在寒冷的泰坦上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On frigid Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.58,0:37:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他們是液態的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they're liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.89,0:37:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,泰坦上有很多水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Titan has lots of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.92,0:37:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但他們都凍的像石頭一樣硬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but all of it is frozen hard as rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.66,0:37:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上 這些風景和山脈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In fact, the landscape and mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.06,0:37:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,都是水做的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are made mainly of water ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.56,0:37:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,零下幾百度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At hundreds of degrees below zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.80,0:37:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,泰坦寒冷得永遠不會有液態的水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Titan is far too cold for water to ever be liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.94,0:37:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,天體生物學家一直在猜想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Astrobiologists since Carl Sagan have wondered
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.17,0:37:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,泰坦上的碳氫化合物湖水中是否有生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if life might swim in Titan's hydrocarbon lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.95,0:37:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,這種生命的化學成分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The chemical basis for such life
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.91,0:37:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,一定和我們所知的都不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would have to be entirely different from anything we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.35,0:37:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的地球生命都需要水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All life on Earth depends on liquid water.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.19,0:38:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,泰坦的表面沒有水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And Titan's surface has none of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.52,0:38:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們可以想像另一種生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But we can imagine other kinds of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.09,0:38:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,這種生物可能呼吸氫氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There might be creatures that inhale hydrogen
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.69,0:38:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是氧氣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}instead of oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.20,0:38:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,呼出甲烷 而不是二氧化碳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And exhale methane instead of carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.70,0:38:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,乙炔可能是他們的能量來源 而不是糖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They might use acetylene instead of sugar as an energy source.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.17,0:38:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我們怎樣才能找到他們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How could we find out if such creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.64,0:38:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他們的帝國躲藏在這石油般的海水下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rule a hidden empire beneath the oil-dark waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.39,0:38:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我們潛下克拉肯海\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're diving down deep into the Kraken Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.70,0:38:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這是以北歐神話中的挪威海怪命名\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}named for the mythic Norse sea monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.07,0:38:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就算真有海怪在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even if there is one of those down there,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.30,0:38:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我們也看不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we probably couldn't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.01,0:38:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,因為太黑了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's so dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.58,0:38:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,把地球上所有的石油和天然氣加起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you took all the oil and natural gas on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.01,0:39:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,也只是泰坦儲量的極小一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it would amount to but a tiny fraction of Titan's reserves.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.25,0:39:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們開點燈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's turn on some lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.49,0:39:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,現在是表面下200米\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're now 200 meters beneath the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.20,0:39:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,看到什麼了嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Did you see something?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.77,0:39:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那邊 通道旁邊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Over there, by that vent.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.01,0:39:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,也許我眼花了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe it was just my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.51,0:39:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們想要確切知道的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I guess we'll have to come back
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.51,0:39:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼我們就必須得再來一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if we want to find out for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.75,0:39:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我想和你再說最後一個故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's one last story I want to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.42,0:39:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,這是最偉大的科學故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's the greatest story science has ever told.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.93,0:39:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,關於我們世界上的生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the story of life on our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.82,0:40:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,歡迎來到40億年前的地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Welcome to the Earth of four billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.96,0:40:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有生命的星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was our planet before life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.66,0:40:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人知道生命如何誕生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nobody knows how life got started.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.76,0:40:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,撞擊和侵蝕摧毀了大部分的證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the evidence from that time was destroyed by impact and erosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.80,0:40:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,科學處在無知和已知之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science works on the frontier between knowledge and ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.61,0:40:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們不怕承認我們不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We're not afraid to admit what we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.57,0:40:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,一點也不丟人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's no shame in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.91,0:40:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,丟人的是我們假裝已經有了答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The only shame is to pretend that we have all the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.78,0:40:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,也許觀眾中有人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe someone watching this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.48,0:40:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,會成為首個解開這個謎題的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will be the first to solve the mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.02,0:40:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,關於地球生命的起源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of how life on Earth began.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.99,0:40:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,從現存的微生物得來的證據顯示\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The evidence from living microbes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.86,0:40:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他們最古老的祖先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}suggest that their earliest ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.80,0:40:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,喜歡高溫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}preferred high temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.53,0:41:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,地球生命也許出現在熱水中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Life on Earth may have arisen in hot water
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.47,0:41:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,被水下的火山口環繞著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}around submerged volcanic vents.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.54,0:41:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,在卡爾·薩根的宇宙節目中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In Carl Sagan's original Cosmos series,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.05,0:41:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他找到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he traced the unbroken thread that stretches
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.85,0:41:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,從將近40億年前的單細胞生物到你之間的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}directly from the one-celled organisms
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.95,0:41:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,不間斷的線索\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of nearly four billion years ago... to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.82,0:41:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,相當於40秒的40億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Four billion years in 40 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.99,0:41:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,從不能分辨晝夜的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From creatures who had yet to discern day from night
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.56,0:41:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,到可以探索宇宙的生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to beings who are exploring the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.52,0:42:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是分子用40億年時間進化的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those are some of the things that molecules do given four billion years of evolution.
